      • collect

        public static Iterable<ICharacterTag> collect(Iterable<ICharacterTag> i1,
                              Iterable<ICharacterTag> i2)
        Create an iterable instance by combining two iterable objects. The iteration order is i1 then i2. Each character will only be visited once. All duplicated characters will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        i1 - first iterable object
        i2 - second iterable object
        Returns:
        combined iterable object

      • collect

        Create an iterable instance by combining two iterable objects. The iteration order is i1 then i2.Each character will only be visited once. All duplicated characters will be ignored.

      • collect

        public static Iterable<ICharacterTag> collect(Iterable<? extends ICharacterReferrer> referrers)
        Create an iterable object from multiple ICharacterReferrer objects. The result consists of all the referred characters by them. Each character will only be visited once. All duplicated characters will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        referrers - multiple ICharacterReferrer objects.
        Returns:
        all the referred character tags

      • filterAndCollect

        public static Iterable<ICharacterTag> filterAndCollect(Iterable<?> iterable)
        Find all the ICharacterReferrer instances from a generic collection. Then, create an iterable object from these ICharacterReferrer objects. The result consists of all the referred characters by them. Each character will only be visited once. All duplicated characters will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        iterable - an iterable object that contains ICharacterReferrer members
        Returns:
        all the referred character tags

      • empty

        public static Iterable<ICharacterTag> empty()
        Always use this empty iterable instead of creating an empty Collection.
        Returns:
        an empty iterable
